title: Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 10/28/09 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
October 28, 2009

 



Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 10/28/09




Nominations sent to the Senate:
Philip E. Coyle, III, of California, to be an Associate Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy, vice Rosina M. Bierbaum.
Lawrence G. Romo, of Texas, to be Director of Selective Service, vice William A. Chatfield, resigned.
